title: Miaderm Fragrance-Free
description: When people who are sensitive to fragrances need radiation therapy, Miaderm Fragrance-Free enables them to protect against skin damage and get relief. Miaderm Fragrance-Free formula Bringing radiation dermatitis relief and protection to all who need it. Some people, including many chemotherapy patients, have a higher sensitivity to fragrances. This often causes them to avoid lotions that are fragrant. Knowing that many radiation patients are or have been in chemotherapy, we developed Miaderm Fragrance-Free so protection and relief from skin damage are available to even those who are challenged by fragrance sensitivity. Miaderm Fragrance-Free is -Based on Miaderm Radiation Relief's scientific formula -Designed for individuals with sensitivity to perfumes or fragrances -Recommended for people with chemical sensitivities -Ideal for patients who've had prior reactions to dermatitis relief lotions -Made in the U.S.A. -100% satisfaction-guaranteed. For best results, begin using Miaderm Radiation Relief Lotion 1 week prior to the start of treatment. Apply Miaderm three to four times daily to areas of skin within the radiation treatment field. Do not use within 1 hour prior to radiation treat CAUTION: For topical external skin use only. Avoid eye contact. Prior to regular use, test lotion on small area on wrist or forearm, if rash, itch, or redness occurs, discontinue use and consult your physician. Does not interfere with radiation therapy effectiveness. INACTIVE INGREDIENTS: Water, Calendula Officinalis Flower Extract, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Dimethicone, Potassium Cetyl Phosphate, Hydrogenated Palm Glycerides, Cetyl Palmitate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Glyceryl Stearate SE, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice (Organic), Soluble Collagen, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Cetearyl Methicone, Butylene Glycol, Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Xanthan Gum, Hexylene Glycol, Disodium EDTA, Ethylhexylglycerin, Caprylyl Glycol, Sodium Benzoate, Phenoxetol, Citric Acid
